name: ADMI Gaming PC: i7 8700, RTX 2060, 16GB 2400MHz, 240GB SSD, 2TB HDD, MB520 Case, 550W PSU, Wifi, Windows 10

q_a.q: does this include an ssd?
q_a.a: Yes. The boot drive is SSD

q_a.q: Can it connect to my wifi wirelessly?
q_a.a: Only if you ask them to put a WiFi card in

q_a.q: Dose this pc have a cd/dvd reader
q_a.a: No it does not

q_a.q: How many USB ports front and back?
q_a.a: I have five USB's on the back and TWO on the top of the PC that are marked SS I assume for Solid State external drives. They work as standard USB-3 inputs also.  Hope this helps.

q_a.q: Does this pc have warranty
q_a.a: Yes

q_a.q: Is the windows 10 installed in the ssd or the hard drive
q_a.a: just the one ssd the other is your storage e drive works better for a fast start up, keep everything separate so make sure you add to the e drive all your programs and save stuff

q_a.q: Hi would this spec run XPlane please?
What graphics card does this have? It says 2070 in the title but 1080 in the description.
q_a.a: The one I brought had a 1080

q_a.q: Does it come with a wifi network card?
q_a.a: Mine didnt. Or bluetooth.  Had to order a wifi / BT dongle

q_a.q: How many USB ports does it have?
Hi dose this pc  have more than 2 usb 3 ports?
does the front panel come off as i don't get how the fans work other wise?

what's the motherboard for the i7 8700 rtx 2070?

can i add a decent wifi card on to it? or do i need to increase the power supply?

Which wifi card would you reccomend for this pc?
Is this system liquid cooled? I saw a post about water cooling, but thats different from liquid cooling.
How many years of warnity does this have ? And if i open the case i lose warnity?
q_a.a: Not sure on that1

q_a.q: does the motherboard for the 1080 250gb ssd version support dual sli with a 1080 and 1080ti
q_a.a: you need to speak to the supply by email they will tell you all for  these questions as each pc has a different spec

q_a.q: What is the return policy, and is there a warranty?
q_a.a: yes to both and warranty is 1year

q_a.q: Would this be OK to leave running for few days at a time constantly?
q_a.a: yes,    no problem with mine its liquid cooled

q_a.q: Could this pc handle iracing?
q_a.a: No idea

q_a.q: I'm confused, please help. some reviews have stated this model comes with 240gb ssd, but i can't see it on the spec. could someone confirm please.
q_a.a: Mine did, 240GB SSD and 2TB HDD

q_a.q: does This have warranty please or is that an extra cost and for how long if so?
q_a.a: I think it has a warranty with it but you can buy a longer one during your purchase

q_a.q: Is the windows on the hdd or the ssd?
q_a.a: The windows is on SSD

q_a.q: How much watts on the PSU?
q_a.a: I think mine has a 750w PSU

q_a.q: Could this pc handle iracing?
q_a.a: It runs Project Cars 2 on ultra settings, so iRacing should be ok.

q_a.q: Does this come with a nvidia geforce gtx 2070? in the product information it says that is it a gtx 1080.
What gtx 1070 is it?
The description refers to a intel core i7-8700 4.6ghz six core cpu processor but the spec refers to intel 68882 4.60ghz processor? which is it?
Does it have hdmi ports and how do i ask them to put in a wifi card?
What is the warranty? Can I add fans etc without voiding it ?
what CPU cooler does it have?
How does the nividia geforce rtx 2070 in this compare with a 1070ti
Is there room for more fans?
What are the dimensions
What frames does it run for fortnite max settings?
Would i be able to put i'm a gtx1080ti 11 gb?
q_a.a: Yes you wouldn’t need to change anything

q_a.q: Does this pc have DVI or the other monitor input?
q_a.a: No DVI on the GTX1080, the onboard graphics dose have DVI

q_a.q: does this pc have a displayport?
q_a.a: Yes, mind had 4 plus 1 hdmi as I recall maybe 3

q_a.q: Can you please post a link or the full name of the motherboard that is used. Thank you :
Is the gtx 1060 3gb or 6gb
q_a.a: Don’t know I bought the GTX1080 8gb version read the description!

q_a.q: Does admi use the stock cooler that comes with the i7 8700 or do they upgrade it?
q_a.a: Not sure

q_a.q: Does it come with windows 10 installed
q_a.a: Yes it's Windows 10 Home

q_a.q: How many sata connections are on the motherboard?
q_a.a: not a clue

q_a.q: What's the motherboard for the i7 8700 gtx 1080?
q_a.a: Asus prime H310m-k in the one I had delivered.

q_a.q: I dont like the sound of fans, is the machine generally silent?
q_a.a: the fans are almost silent

for the GTX 1080 570X what motherboard and 1080?

reviews.content:
Great machine.
Plenty of power & memory for the price.
Solidly built with all the bells & whistles expected of this type of machine.
Although built for gaming, I mostly use it for other stuff because of it's technical specs are so good.
added photos  top top pc

Well configured, professionally built. Seems great price for this quality of components. Fans only have one lighting setting, a red ring as circumference of the 120mm fans. Would definitely recommend for high end performance
First gaming PC I’ve owned. Using it mainly for Oculus Rift so far. Everything is awesome. Communication with seller, delivery, packaging, PC - great stuff.
Fast delivery,  the item was as described.  The computer works well and is quiet in operation. Seems a good buy
Great start up time & loading apps fast.

What a brilliant quality gaming machine this is. To have a SSD and 2 TB HDD and GTX  1080 makes it a no brainier for the price. Straight out of the box and ready to go. I use it mainly for X-Plane 11 with extra scenery. All settings for the textures, graphics, shadows and reflections on max setting.  Very pleased with this purchase as we are with the one we bought in February for my son.
very happy
Very powerfull pc happy with purchase. Only downside is no Wifi card which the seller is saying not recommended to use with high speed gaming rather use ethernet cable network.
great gaming pc can run everything on ultra and the support from the seller was great
